## Pass 2: Presentation Strategy

### 2.1 Framework (Choose ONE)

| Framework | Structure | Best When |
|-----------|-----------|-----------|
| **Pyramid** | Recommendation â†’ Arguments â†’ Evidence â†’ Action | Answer-first |
| **SCR** | Situation â†’ Complication â†’ Resolution â†’ Implications | Problem-solving |
| **Transformation** | Old World â†’ Disruption â†’ New World â†’ Imperatives | Before/after |
| **Countdown** | Stakes â†’ Deadline â†’ Readiness â†’ Action | Urgency |
| **Evidence Cascade** | Foundation â†’ Build â†’ Conclusion â†’ Action | Data-rich case |

**Selection**: [Framework] â€” [Why]

### 2.2 Opening Hook (Choose ONE)

| Hook | Pattern |
|------|---------|
| **Number** | Lead with striking statistic |
| **Question** | Provocative question |
| **Stakes** | Quantified risk/opportunity |
| **Shift** | "Everything changed when..." |
| **Contrast** | "While X... Y..." |

**Selection**: [Hook] â€” [Why]

### 2.3 Closing (Choose ONE)

| Technique | Pattern |
|-----------|---------|
| **Callback** | Return to opening |
| **Choice** | "Two paths..." |
| **Imperative** | Direct call to action |
| **Timeline** | "By [date]..." |
| **Question** | What matters most |

**Selection**: [Technique] â€” [Why]

